Definition.WordDefinition:
advised \ad*vised"\ adj. 1. 1 Carefully thought out; likely to be the best course; -- said of actions. Often used in combination; as, ill-advised, well-advised. Also See: wise {unadvised, ill-advised}
Syn: considered, well-advised [WordNet 1.5]
2. Having received information; as, be kept advised. {uninformed} [WordNet 1.5]
